## Manifest convention (v0.5.1)

Every key in `knowledge/paths-manifest.json` `paths` ‚à™ `collections` is **leaf XOR namespace** ‚Äî never both. Enforced by `tests/manifest-convention.test.js` in the knowledge repo.

Example:

- ‚úì `accessibility.guide` (leaf) + `accessibility.index` (leaf, sibling) ‚Äî coexist cleanly
- ‚úó `accessibility` (leaf) + `accessibility.index` (prefix of nested children) ‚Äî would collide

Pre-v0.5.1 had the collision form; v0.5.1 renamed `accessibility` ‚Üí `accessibility.guide` and `collections.components.categoryDefaults` ‚Üí `collections.components.categoryDefaults.byKey` to honor the rule.

