## How drift is detected

The docs site runs four build-time guards on every vendor refresh:

1. **Motion-ref resolution** ‚Äî every `motion_refs[].ref` cited by a category MD must resolve against `tokens/motion.json#patterns` by `.slug`. Build fails if not.
2. **A11y-ref resolution** ‚Äî every `accessibility[].ref` must resolve against `a11y-index.json#sections`. Build fails if not.
3. **ASCII operator check** ‚Äî vendored MD code-fenced blocks must use ASCII operators (`=>`, `->`, `<=`, `>=`, `!==`). Build fails on Unicode equivalents inside code blocks.
4. **Schema-version match** ‚Äî `_schema_version` in `paths-manifest.json` must equal the version this site expects (currently `1`). Build fails on mismatch.

Failed guards block the vendor PR from auto-merging, surfacing drift in human-reviewable form.
